               <p>MICHAEL FRANCIS TINDALE. I am a <rs id="t18340904-76-viclabel417" type="occupation">cabinet-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-76-victim499 t18340904-76-viclabel417"></join>, and keep a shop in <placeName id="t18340904-76-crimeloc418">Ratcliff-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-76-crimeloc418" type="placeName" value="Ratcliff-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-76-crimeloc418" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-76-off415 t18340904-76-crimeloc418"></join>. On the 24th of July, I was returning home; and when I was opposite my own shop, I saw the prisoner coming out with the caddy under his arm - I went and asked if it had been sold - they said "No" - I then followed the prisoner - some persons called out, "There is a gentleman behind you" - the prisoner then turned, and threw it down - I took him - the caddy was picked up and given to me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you see any one in the shop with me? A. No: I saw you in the shop with it under your left arm.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340904-76-person500">
                  JOHN 
